_meanings:
{@--1@} As a gentle address
in the sense of ‘friend’, ‘oh’ ‘ah’
({#komalAmaMtraRe#}); or simply as a 
vocative particle; {#ayi#} 
{#vivekaviSrAMtamaBihitaM#} <ls>M. 1</ls>; {#ayi kaWora#} <ls>U. 3. 27</ls> Oh
you ruthless one; {#ayi Bo maharziputra#}
<ls>Ś. 7</ls>; {#ayi vidyutpramadAnAM tvamapi ca duHKaM#}
{#na jAnAsi#} <ls>Mk. 5. 32</ls>; {#ayi#} 
{#mAtardevayajanasaMBave devi sIte#} <ls>U. 4</ls>; see also  
<ls>Bv. 1. 5</ls>, <ls n="Bv. 1.">11</ls>, <ls n="Bv. 1.">44.</ls>

{@--2@} As a particle of
entreaty or solicitation ({#anunaya#}),
‘I pray’, ‘prythee’; {#ayi saMprati dehi#}
{#darSanaM#} <ls>Ku. 4. 28</ls>; also of encouragement
or persuasion; {#ayi maMdasmitamaDuraM vadanaM#}
{#tanvaMgi yadi manAkkuruze#} <ls>Bv. 2. 150.</ls>

{@--3@} As a particle of gentle or kind
inquiry ({#praSna#}); {#ayi jIvitanATa jIvasi#}
<ls>Ku. 4. 3</ls>; {#ayIdamevaM parihAsaH#} <ls n="Ku.">5. 62</ls>;
{#ayi jAnIze roBilasya sArTavAhasya gfhaM#}
